metadata.name: Royal Iris
metadata.description:
The word 'iris' stands for 'rainbow' in Greek

According to the Greek legends, Iris was a goddess that carried messages between human beings and gods. She is said to travel on the rainbow while carrying messages from the gods to mortals. The symbolic meaning of the Iris is thus ‘I have a message for you’.

Other symbols: faith, hope, courage, wisdom and admiration.
